    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison hoped to hear Mrs. Abby Kelley Foster&apos;s explanation of how she came to be &quot;grievously wounded&quot; by a remark that he made at the New England Convention. Garrison writes: &quot;I hear tht you believe or suppose that I attributed to you intentional dishonesty in the manner of procuring money of prominent members of the Republican party.&quot; Garrison repudiates the accusation. Garrison &quot;neither impeached, nor meant to impeach&quot; Foster&apos;s integrity. He admires Foster&apos;s &quot;character and moral heroism&quot; and holds their friendship, of more than a quarter of century, dear to his heart.</subfield>
